
[1]occurrence

   OCCUR'RENCE, n.

   1. Literally, a coming or happening; hence, any incident or accidental
   event; that which happens without being designed or expected; any
   single event. We speak of an unusual occurrence, or of the ordinary
   occurrences of life.

   2. Occasional presentation.

   Voyages detain the mind by the perpetual occurrence and expectation of
   something new.
